# Lore Foundation

Project Genesis: Archive takes place after the collapse-era sanctuary systems have survived long enough to begin restoring and cataloging life.

The Archive is not a trophy case. It is a scientific, cultural, and ethical continuity system. Every organism registered into the Archive represents a recovered branch of biological memory.

## Tone

Epic, hopeful, dangerous, mysterious, scientific.

The wonder is earned, not magical.

## Core Image

Sanctuary One at first light. Tundra Node Alpha under aurora. A reconstructed mammoth herd moves across recovered tundra while Warden Cell field operators maintain the containment perimeter. Archive-cyan telemetry overlays the amber glow of sanctuary habitat lighting.
